            "markup": "\u003Ch2\u003EWhat is Codegarden?\u003C/h2\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIf you\u0027ve never been, let me try to explain what Codegarden actually is, because it\u0027s hard to do it justice.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn paper, it\u0027s the official Umbraco conference, run by Umbraco HQ once a year. There are keynotes, talks across multiple stages, a roadmap session where you find out what\u0027s coming next in the CMS, the MVP awards, and the package awards.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThere are lots of talks by fellow community members and experts from other communities, all coming together to share knowledge.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EYou learn loads and meet lots of new people. You come away with new techniques and new ways of thinking, and a head full of ideas you can\u0027t wait to try when you get home.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThere is a gala dinner on the Thursday evening where they play Bingo, for prizes that you probably don\u0027t want to win. But you have to be there to understand just how fun and crazy it is.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHere are some of the talks from Codegarden 2026:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
